g.text: The present study demonstrates that a robust EG can be gener-
ated at the heterointerface of an epitaxially grown CHO ﬁlm and
a STO substrate with either termination. This EG is distinctly
the termination of STO, has no strict critical thickness of CHO,
and is stable against polar adsorbates. This EG is also remarkably
stable against annealing in oxygen, comparable with that of
/T-STO. Using this EG as the conducting channel, and
CHO as gating dielectrics, FETs are constructed. The high-
performance gating ability, integrated with the robustness to
makes the EG at the interfaces of CHO/STO very attractive for
